{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}} {{Use British English|date=May 2015}} [[File:Adrian Hopkins 1894-1967.jpg|thumbnail|Adrian Hopkins MC]] Major '''Adrian Edmund Hopkins''' [[Military Cross|MC]] (8 October 1894 – 1 March 1967) was a British [[philatelist]] who signed the [[Roll of Distinguished Philatelists]] in 1947.<ref>''[http://www.abps.org.uk/Awards/Roll_of_Distinguished_Philatelists/RDP_Background_20111231_LR.pdf Background notes on The Roll of Distinguished Philatelists September 2011]'', Roll of Distinguished Philatelists Trust, London, 2011. [https://www.webcitation.org/6OlHSBOTl Archived here.]</ref> He was wounded during World War I and lost an arm. Hopkins was the President and a founder member of the Postal History Society and three times [[Mayor of Bath]] (1937, 1938 and 1953).<ref name=abps>[http://www.abps.org.uk/Home/Who_Was_Who/index.xalter#H Who Was Who in British Philately], [[Association of British Philatelic Societies]], 2014. Retrieved 1 May 2014. [https://www.webcitation.org/5zDx9UBpl Archived here.]</ref>
==Selected publications== *''Talks about postage stamps - Philately in Bristol''. 1927. *''A history of wreck covers originating at sea, on land, and in the air''. 1940.
