{{Infobox Officeholder |honorific-prefix = |name = Arnao Esterlin |honorific-suffix = |image = |imagesize = |smallimage = |alt = |caption = |order = |office = |term_start = |term_end = |president = |birth_date = 1510s |birth_place = [[Flanders]] |death_date = 1593 |death_place = [[Asuncion]], [[Paraguay]] |restingplace = |restingplacecoordinates = |birthname = |nationality =[[File:Flag of Flanders.svg|border|20px]] [[Flemish]] |party = |otherparty = |spouse = |relations = |children = |residence = |alma_mater = |occupation = [[Conquistador]] |profession = [[artilleryman]] |cabinet = |committees = |portfolio = |religion = Catholicism |signature = |signature_alt = |footnotes = }} '''Arnao Esterlin''' (16th Century) was a Flemish conquistador, he was among those who approved the election of Captain [[Domingo Martínez de Irala]], for Lieutenant Governor of Asuncion.<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Los Conquistadores del Río de la Plata|publisher=Ricardo de Lafuente Machaín|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=ZP9kAAAAMAAJ&q=arnaos+esterlin+conquistadores&dq=arnaos+esterlin+conquistadores&hl=es-419&sa=X&ei=XmTMVNXxDYScNtrMg-AG&ved=0CCcQ6AEwAQ|accessdate= }}</ref>
== Biography ==
Born in [[Flanders]], Esterlín arrival at [[Rio de la Plata]] as a [[Artillery|gunner]] in the expedition of [[Pedro de Mendoza]].<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Bulletin de l'Institut historique belge de Rome - Volumen44|publisher=Institut historique belge de Rome|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=-eHvAAAAMAAJ&q=arnaos+terlin+buenos+aires&dq=arnaos+terlin+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ei=eWvMVIb0L4inNqOxhKAJ&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA|accessdate= }}</ref> Arnao was the son of Cristóbal Esterlin (Osterling) and Ana Bersthin, (natives of [[Germany]]). He had three natural children with a woman, native of Asuncion.<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Beiträge zur Geschichte und Kultur der Stadt Nürnberg, Volume 11, Issue 1|publisher=Stadtbibliothek, 1967|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=UN4_AQAAIAAJ&q=arnaos+esterlin+buenos+aires&dq=arnaos+esterlin+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ei=KWTMVIaYKMOngwS-moPICw&ved=0CDgQ6AEwBA|accessdate= }}</ref> His son Rodrigo de Esterlín, was married to Juana, daughter of Zoilo de Solorzano, (conquistador born in [[Biscay|Vizcaya]]).<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Genealogía, Números 14-15|publisher=Instituto Argentino de Ciencias Genealógicas.|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?ei=3mzMVIbgFZLvgwTwsIGQCA&hl=es&id=oCUrAQAAIAAJ&dq=rodrigo+de+esterlin+asuncion&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=esterlin|accessdate= }}</ref>
